    archetype: "The Pre-Professional Powerhouse with the Collaborative Soul",

    oneSentenceSummary: "Northwestern is the elite private university that managed to build top-ranked professional schools in journalism, engineering, music, and communication alongside a research university — with a quarter system, a lakefront campus in Evanston, and a collaborative culture that its 7% acceptance rate does not imply.",

    pipeline: "7% acceptance rate for the Class of 2029 — 3,710 admitted from 53,000+ applications. #6 nationally among National Universities by US News 2025. Six undergraduate schools, each with its own admissions process: Weinberg College of Arts and Sciences, McCormick School of Engineering, Medill School of Journalism, School of Communication, School of Education and Social Policy, and Bienen School of Music. The school-specific application is the single most consequential strategic decision in the Northwestern file — applicants are evaluated through the lens of their chosen school, not as general admits. Medill is the #1 journalism program in America. McCormick consistently ranks top-20 in engineering nationally. 260,000+ alumni network.",

    hiddenPathway: "The quarter system is Northwestern's most undersurfaced educational architecture. Four 10-week quarters per year rather than two semesters means students take more courses across more subjects, can double major or add a minor more easily, and graduate with a breadth of intellectual formation that semester schools cannot match in four years. The Integrated Marketing Communications certificate — available to all Northwestern undergraduates, not only Medill students — is one of the most practical professional credentials any non-business student can acquire alongside their major: data-driven marketing strategy built on customer insight, developed at Medill and now used by virtually every major brand. The Honors Program in Medical Education (HPME) admits a small cohort of undergraduates who are guaranteed admission to Feinberg School of Medicine upon completion of undergraduate requirements — one of the most direct and most selective pre-medicine pathways at any private university in America.",

    institutionalSecret: "",

    theRoom: "8,000 undergraduates on a 240-acre campus on the Lake Michigan shoreline in Evanston — a city of 75,000 immediately north of Chicago. The campus ends at the lake; there is a research pier. The collaborative culture is consistently named as Northwestern's defining characteristic by students and faculty alike — the competitive sorting environment of peer institutions is not replicated here. Big Ten athletics coexist with an academically elite student body in a way that distinguishes Northwestern from most peer private universities. Chicago is 12 miles south and accessible by Metra train or the Purple Line El — students do not need a car to access one of the most economically and culturally significant cities in America.",

    lifestyle: "Evanston functions as a college town that happens to be a real city — restaurants, arts, and neighborhoods that exist independently of the university give the campus a less insular character than peer schools in smaller towns. Lake Michigan is the visual and recreational backdrop. The social life is less Greek-dominated than most peer universities.",

