    archetype: "The Evangelical Research University of the Los Angeles Basin",

    oneSentenceSummary: "Azusa Pacific University is the largest evangelical Christian university in California — a comprehensive university of 10,000 students 26 miles east of downtown Los Angeles, with doctoral programs in nursing, education, psychology, and business, and a distinctive strength in training Christian leaders for the Los Angeles ministry, healthcare, and social services ecosystem.",

    pipeline: "Nursing — one of the largest nursing programs in California, producing registered nurses who feed every major Los Angeles and San Gabriel Valley hospital system. Education — top credentialing program in the Inland Empire and San Gabriel Valley, producing teachers and administrators for some of California's most diverse and under-resourced districts. Psychology and Counseling — APU produces a significant share of Southern California's licensed clinical social workers and marriage and family therapists. Business — undergraduate and graduate business programs with regional placement in the Los Angeles market. Music — the Department of Music is the largest evangelical Christian music program on the West Coast, producing worship leaders, music educators, and recording professionals. Social Work — direct placement into Los Angeles County's extensive nonprofit and social services infrastructure. 6,500 undergraduates; 10,000 total enrollment including graduate.",

    hiddenPathway: "APU's most underappreciated strategic position is its role as the primary training institution for Christian healthcare workers, counselors, and educators in one of the most complex and underserved urban regions in America. Los Angeles County has the largest homeless population in America, the largest immigrant population in America, and some of the deepest educational inequity in America. APU graduates go into these systems with professional credentials, language skills, and a faith-motivated service orientation that makes them exceptionally effective. The demand for APU nursing, counseling, and social work graduates in the LA Basin is structural and growing.",

    institutionalSecret: "APU is the most comprehensive evangelical university in California — offering doctoral programs in nursing, education, psychology, physical therapy, and business — and it is almost entirely invisible in mainstream college counseling conversations. For a student who wants a Christian university environment, a research university level of academic infrastructure, and proximity to Los Angeles, APU offers a combination that no other institution in California provides.",

    theRoom: "Main campus in Azusa, in the San Gabriel Valley 26 miles east of downtown Los Angeles. APU also operates the Azusa Pacific Online campus and regional centers across Southern California. The student body is among the most racially and ethnically diverse of any evangelical university in America — reflecting the demographics of Los Angeles County itself. 45% of students identify as students of color. The Wesleyan evangelical tradition is active and communal but not culturally narrow.",

    lifestyle: "Azusa is a working-class San Gabriel Valley city — not a glamorous college town — but Los Angeles is 26 miles west, the San Gabriel Mountains are immediately north, and the full cultural and professional infrastructure of the LA Basin is accessible. Students who engage Los Angeles get four years in the most culturally complex, professionally diverse, and entertainingly rich metropolitan area in America.",

