    oneSentenceSummary: "Seattle Pacific University is a Free Methodist liberal arts university of 3,800 students in the Queen Anne neighborhood of Seattle — combining a rigorous Christian academic tradition with direct access to one of America's most consequential technology and social impact ecosystems.",

    pipeline: "Business and Economics — SPU's School of Business and Economics places graduates into Amazon, Microsoft, Boeing, Starbucks, and the Seattle nonprofit sector. Education — SPU's School of Education is one of the most respected teacher preparation programs in Washington State. Nursing — top-ranked in Washington, feeding Swedish Medical Center, UW Medicine, and Seattle Children's Hospital. Psychology and Counseling — SPU produces a disproportionate share of Pacific Northwest licensed counselors and social workers. Computer Science and Engineering — growing placement in the Seattle technology corridor. 3,800 undergraduates; 4,200 total enrollment.",

