    hiddenPathway: "Silicon Slopes is the most undersurfaced career ecosystem in American higher education. The 14-mile corridor from Salt Lake City to Provo hosts over 10,000 technology companies, including Qualtrics (acquired by SAP for $8B), Adobe's North American engineering hub, Domo, and a concentration of SaaS, fintech, and enterprise software companies that rivals Austin and Seattle at a fraction of the cost of living. University of Utah engineering, computing, and business graduates enter this ecosystem through a pipeline that is structurally advantaged. The U of U's technology transfer office has produced more startup companies per research dollar spent than any other public university in America for multiple consecutive years.",
