    oneSentenceSummary: "Western Colorado University is a small public liberal arts university of 3,100 students in Gunnison — one of the most remote and spectacular settings of any university in America, 9 miles from Crested Butte ski resort, offering nationally recognized programs in outdoor recreation management, environmental studies, and business in a mountain community where the curriculum and the landscape are inseparable.",
    pipeline: "Recreation and Sport Pedagogy — Western's outdoor recreation and adventure education programs are among the most respected in the Mountain West, feeding ski resort management, outdoor education, adventure tourism, and outdoor industry careers. Business Administration — the School of Business produces graduates for regional Colorado markets and, through the MBA program, outdoor industry leadership. Environmental Studies — direct field access to the Gunnison Basin, Black Canyon of the Gunnison, and the West Elk Wilderness. Education — teacher preparation for rural Colorado schools. Psychology — strong counseling and human services track. 2,600 undergraduates; 3,100 total.",
    hiddenPathway: "Crested Butte is 9 miles from the Western campus — one of the most renowned ski resorts in Colorado, with a mountain culture that is authentically local rather than resort-commercial. Western students have access to one of the great ski mountains in America as a practical laboratory for ski patrol, resort management, outdoor education, and ski industry careers. The Gunnison Basin is also one of the premier fly-fishing destinations in Colorado — feeding a recreation economy that produces outdoor industry professionals with hands-on expertise that no urban university can replicate. The Taylor River and East River fisheries are world-class and accessible from campus.",
    institutionalSecret: "Gunnison records the coldest average winter temperatures of any city in the continental United States — colder than Anchorage in most years. The Gunnison Basin sits in a thermal inversion pocket at 7,703 feet that produces legendary cold and legendary snow. This is not a liability for Western students — it is a selection filter. The students who choose Western understand that they are choosing a specific kind of life for four years, and the community that forms around that shared choice is unusually tight, unusually purposeful, and unusually resistant to the social anxieties that consume students at more conventional institutions.",
    theRoom: "Gunnison is a ranching and outdoor recreation town of 6,400 people — one of the smallest cities hosting a four-year university in Colorado. The Western campus sits at the edge of town with the Gunnison River, the mountains, and the sky as the immediate context. 2,600 undergraduates who are there by deliberate choice. The social world is small, known, and authentic. There is nowhere to hide and no reason to.",
    lifestyle: "Crested Butte 9 miles north. Black Canyon of the Gunnison 60 miles west. The Taylor River and East River for fly fishing. Hartman Rocks mountain bike trail system adjacent to campus — one of the finest in Colorado. Curecanti National Recreation Area for kayaking. The outdoor life is not an amenity at Western — it is the reason for being there. Gunnison winters are severe by any measure. Students who cannot embrace that are at the wrong institution.",
